# Documentation synchronization

This is a workspace-only rule. Whenever a change in this repository modifies
the system architecture, component responsibilities, data flow, persistence
behavior, public interfaces, SQL syntax, SQL semantics, supported commands,
or SQL examples:

- Update the relevant Markdown files in the same change. At minimum, check
  `README.md` for architecture and public behavior changes and
  `SQL_COMMANDS.md` for SQL command or syntax changes.
- Keep diagrams, project-layout descriptions, command examples, and SQL
  examples consistent with the implementation.
- If no existing Markdown file is the right location, create a focused one
  under the repository rather than leaving the behavior undocumented.
- Do not claim the work is complete until the documentation diff has been
  reviewed alongside the code diff.

For changes unrelated to architecture or SQL behavior, do not edit Markdown
just to satisfy this rule. Documentation updates must describe behavior that
actually exists in the code.
